"Poured into a Gulden Draak tulip. Pours a light to medium golden amber with a one finger white head with good retention and light lacing. Aroma of saison style yeast, clove, light bready malt, apple juice; spicy. Flavor is Belgian saison style yeast, clove, hint of funk, then developing a lightly buttery, bready malt flavor for a melded malt and Belgian style finish. Medium bodied with light creaminess. A successful hybrid of American blonde and Belgian pale styles, combining the dry start of Belgian yeast and spicing with the lightly buttery blonde malt. Nicely done. Blondes tend to be a bit pedestrian for me, but I liked this combination of styles quite a bit. Another winner from this interesting Beer Camp box."
"Overall, this is one of my more preferred beers out of the pack, as the brewers at RR and SN have managed to find that sweet spot between the two quintessential characters of American and Belgian approaches--hops and yeast. And with both, they manage to infuse them without letting one overpower the other, so this stays firmly out of the IPA/Tripel hybrid that is the Belgian IPA. Instead, you have a much easier drinking, but nicely interesting beer."
