"12 ounce bottle into tulip glass, bottled on 6/2/2014. Pours slightly hazy bright gold color with a 1 finger dense white head with good retention, that reduces to a thin cap that lingers. Light spotty soapy lacing clings on the glass, with a moderate amount of streaming carbonation. Aromas of lemon, banana, pear, apple, white grape, clove, pepper, light bubblegum, cracker, bread, herbal, grass, and yeast earthiness. Very nice aromas with good balance and complexity of fruity/spicy yeast, pale malt, and light earthy hop notes; with good strength. Taste of lemon, banana, pear, apple, white grape, clove, pepper, bubblegum, cracker, bread, herbal, grass, and yeast earthiness. Moderate yeast spice/hop bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of lemon, banana, pear, apple, white grape, bubblegum, clove, pepper, cracker, bread, herbal, grass, and yeast earthiness on the finish for a good bit. Damn nice complexity and balance of fruity/spicy yeast, pale malt, and earthy hop flavors; with a nice crisp malt/yeast spice balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and light-medium bodied; with a very smooth and crisp mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is well hidden with minimal warming present after the finish. Overall this is a very nice Belgian pale ale! All around good complexity of fruity/spicy yeast, pale malt, and earthy hop flavors; and very smooth and crisp to drink. A very enjoyable offering."
