"This is a pale crystal-clear gold with a head that quickly fades away to almost nothing. The aroma, however, is pretty nice, spicy-phenolic, hoppy, with a light fruitiness. The flavor is a nice change from the other beers I've had in the collection: this one is well-balanced and interesting, with a clean but stead maltiness, deliciously yeasty-spicy character that gives a little pepperiness (is there coriander in here too? It tastes like it to me, but it might be the yeast character), with light but very ripe fruitiness. This is a very well-done Belgian-style, that doesn't adhere to any particular style but which is interesting and very drinkable."
